47:59.376 --> 48:13.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now to our "NewsHour" Shares,
something that
caught our eye that may be of
interest to

48:13.557 --> 48:15.326 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you, too.

48:15.359 --> 48:20.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An image of a man listening to a
gramophone
in his bombed-out Aleppo home
recently went

48:20.231 --> 48:26.504 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
viral, captured by Agence
France-Presse photographer
Joseph Eid while on assignment
in Syria.

48:26.537 --> 48:31.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We recently spoke to him via
Skype about the
photo and about the man at its
center.

48:31.942 --> 48:38.182 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOSEPH EID, Agence
France-Presse: Well, Mr.
Mohammed, his full name, it's
Mohammed Mohiedin

48:38.215 --> 48:39.183 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Anis.

48:39.216 --> 48:40.951 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And they call him Abu Omar.

48:40.985 --> 48:47.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We saw that this is a very
educated person,
he speaks five languages, he
five years of

48:47.725 --> 48:52.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
medicine in Spain, and he
inherited a great
wealth from his parents.

48:52.596 --> 48:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's one of the richest, very
wealthy people
of Aleppo.

48:56.333 --> 49:03.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Mr. Omar has a very strong
inclination
to collect old and vintage cars,
especially

49:03.107 --> 49:06.877 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
American-made ones from the '40s
and '50s.

49:06.911 --> 49:11.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he told us that how he lost
everything
now and how he was willing to
restart again

49:11.682 --> 49:18.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from ashes, how an old man, a
70-year-old
man, that he is willing to go
back again and

49:18.589 --> 49:25.296 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to reopen his firm and to
restore his house
and to fix his cars, that he
calls they are

49:25.329 --> 49:29.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
injured and they are crying now,
they are
weeping.

49:29.400 --> 49:32.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we went also up to the
master bedroom.

49:32.570 --> 49:38.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When we were there, we barely
could walk amongst
the rubble there inside.

49:38.209 --> 49:39.743 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And we asked him.

49:39.777 --> 49:40.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's still living there.

49:40.778 --> 49:43.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's still sleeping amongst the
rubble.

49:43.080 --> 49:44.415 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's amazing.

49:44.448 --> 49:45.983 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I couldn't believe.

49:46.016 --> 49:49.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yusef (ph), the videographer,
asked him, the
phonograph is still operating?

49:49.787 --> 49:53.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said, "Well, it's the only
thing that still
operates here."

49:53.390 --> 49:55.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, he said: "Wait.

49:55.726 --> 49:56.827 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I will show you.

49:56.861 --> 49:58.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I will let you listen to one of
my favorite
discs."

49:58.929 --> 50:06.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When he ended up explaining
about the song,
he just -- like, he was
transferred.

50:06.670 --> 50:12.309 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was puffing on his pipe and
looking out
from the window.

50:12.343 --> 50:18.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he put his one leg over one
another, and
just like he was by himself
listening to the

50:18.916 --> 50:22.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
music, without taking notice
that we are around
him.

50:22.553 --> 50:25.089 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That moment, like, I was like
electroshock.

50:25.122 --> 50:27.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he didn't notice that I was
taking pictures
of him.

50:27.658 --> 50:30.060 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He was like in another era.

50:30.094 --> 50:35.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He went back to his old good
times, I think.

50:35.799 --> 50:41.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The destruction, the rubble, the
windows,
and the light even which struck
from the left,

50:41.906 --> 50:43.974 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it was so dramatic, you know?

50:44.008 --> 50:48.078 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, it touched me, and I took
the image.

50:48.112 --> 50:53.684 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People are fed up from violence,
from killing,
from beheading, from ISIS.

50:53.717 --> 50:56.654 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They have been hearing it on a
daily basis.

50:56.687 --> 51:03.894 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think this image that it
shows the human
being in Syria, and it gives
also a message

51:03.928 --> 51:05.562 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of hope.

51:05.596 --> 51:11.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He told us: "No matter what
happens to me
or to Syria, I'm not leaving
here.

51:11.669 --> 51:14.438 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's here where I born, and I'm
